# Cloudflare Pages headers config. One rule per block, path + indented
# header lines. Glob '*' supported.
#
# Strategy: 'no-store' on every asset. The browser never writes the
# response to disk and the bfcache is bypassed, so a plain reload (or
# even a back/forward navigation) always fetches the live deploy.
# Trade-off vs. 'max-age=0, must-revalidate': we lose the 304 short
# circuit, so every visit re-downloads the full payload. The site is
# small (data.json ~1 MB, the rest <50 KB) and the project's whole
# point is showing fresh data after a push, so the cost is fine.

/*.html
  Cache-Control: no-store

/*.json
  Cache-Control: no-store

/*.js
  Cache-Control: no-store

/*.css
  Cache-Control: no-store

# Security headers — site is read-only static, no auth, no forms.
#
# CSP notes:
# - script-src 'self' (no inline scripts in any file; app.js loads from
#   same origin) — kills the main XSS vector dead.
# - style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' — index.html and app.js use inline
#   style="…" for a handful of one-off touches. Accepted: CSS-only XSS
#   has very limited impact on a read-only site without auth.
# - img-src 'self' data: — favicon is an inline SVG via data: URI.
# - external INE / Wikipedia links are navigational (<a href>), not
#   embedded resources, so they don't need CSP allowances.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https://*.basemaps.cartocdn.com; connect-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=()
